Post Installation
=================

1. Load the GTK Plugin

Create the file ~/.config/xfce4/xinitrc

{{{
#!/bin/sh

export GTK_MODULES=globalmenu-gnome
. /etc/xdg/xfce4/xinitrc
}}}

2. Add the XFCE Plugin to the panel or

Try http://bapoumba.wordpress.com/2008/01/04/add-gnome-applets-to-the-xfce-panel/
(Not tested) with the GNOME Applet

The XFCE applet is a stub and unmaintained. Feel free to take it and make it stronger.

